  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Voice to the People II - CLSD Cost Extension</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Building active citizenship
2). Enhance Voice: Voice and representation of women and other socially excluded groups are enhanced
3). Fostering Institutionalized state-citizen actions
4). Adaptive learning</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The cost extension of the V2P programme seeks to improve how State and local government responsively engages the voice of citizens, community demands and civil society representation and scrutiny; and improves delivery of services, responsiveness and inclusive budgeting and planning. The extension will help embed and deepen result by covering Anambra at scale from 12LGA to 21LGA and broaden at across the south east with Enugu as the hub as well as test the learning in a Northern state-Kaduna. The objectives of the extension is to provide resources to enable the programme to;
1). Building active citizenship.
2). ENHANCE VOICE: Voice and representation of women and other socially excluded groups are enhanced
3). Fostering Institutionalized state-citizen actions.
4). Adaptive learning</narrative>
  </description>
